<https://w3id.org/ficr#hasConditionState> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a boundary condition record to its assessed condition state, such as effective, compromised, or unknown."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#hasConditionState> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "hasConditionState"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ficr#hasConnectionWith
<https://w3id.org/ficr#hasConnectionWith> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#hasConnectionWith> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "indicates that the two individuals have a passageway."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#hasConnectionWith> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "hasConnectionWith"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ficr#hasEvidenceStatus
<https://w3id.org/ficr#hasEvidenceStatus> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#hasEvidenceStatus> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/ficr#EvidenceStatus> .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#hasEvidenceStatus> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links an assessment finding, boundary condition record, or other assessment-related record to a controlled evidence status. The domain is intentionally left open to avoid forcing all evidence-qualified records into the AssessmentFinding hierarchy."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#hasEvidenceStatus> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "hasEvidenceStatus"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ficr#hasFireRiskUnitRole
<https://w3id.org/ficr#hasFireRiskUnitRole> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
