# https://w3id.org/ficr#Assessment
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Assessment> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Assessment> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A fire-related assessment record produced through an O&M task. It may represent compliance checking, risk analysis, or inspection assessment and can produce assessment findings."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Assessment> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Assessment"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ficr#AssessmentBasis
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AssessmentBasis> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AssessmentBasis> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A bundle of evidence items used to justify a fire compliance evaluation or risk assessment. It groups observed site evidence, regulatory sources, and supporting external documents for traceability and explanation."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AssessmentBasis> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "AssessmentBasis"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ficr#AssessmentFinding
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AssessmentFinding> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AssessmentFinding> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A record produced by an assessment to capture a compliance, risk, or inspection finding concerning an assessed element, system, zone, risk unit, requirement, or scenario. Findings may be linked to evidence, evidence status, and assessment results where applicable."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AssessmentFinding> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "AssessmentFinding"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ficr#AssessmentState
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AssessmentState> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AssessmentState> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An abstract superclass for controlled state or result values used in FiCR assessments, including boundary condition states, operational impairment states, evidence states, applicability states, and compliance results. Subclasses retain their domain-specific meanings and are not merged."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AssessmentState> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "AssessmentState"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ficr#AtriumSpace
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AtriumSpace> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AtriumSpace> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/bot#Space> .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AtriumSpace> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#disjointWith> <https://w3id.org/ficr#BalconySpace> .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AtriumSpace> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#disjointWith> <https://w3id.org/ficr#CavitySpace> .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AtriumSpace> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#disjointWith> <https://w3id.org/ficr#DuctSpace> .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AtriumSpace> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#disjointWith> <https://w3id.org/ficr#RoofSpace> .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AtriumSpace> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#disjointWith> <https://w3id.org/ficr#RoomSpace> .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AtriumSpace> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#disjointWith> <https://w3id.org/ficr#ShaftSpace> .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AtriumSpace> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#disjointWith> <https://w3id.org/ficr#StairSpace> .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AtriumSpace> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A continuous space that passes through one or more structural floors within a building, not necessarily vertically.\r\nEnclosed lift wells, enclosed escalator wells, building services ducts and stairs are not classified as atria."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AtriumSpace> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "AtriumSpace"@en .
