# 
<https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8020-4609> <http://www.w3.org/2006/vcard/ns#fn> "Pieter Pauwels" .
<https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8020-4609> <https://schema.org/name> "Pieter Pauwels" .
# 
<https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2033-859X> <http://www.w3.org/2006/vcard/ns#fn> "Georg Ferdinand Schneider" .
<https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2033-859X> <https://schema.org/name> "Georg Ferdinand Schneider" .
# 
<https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6519-7057> <http://www.w3.org/2006/vcard/ns#fn> "Mads Holten Rasmussen" .
<https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6519-7057> <https://schema.org/name> "Mads Holten Rasmussen" .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AccessRoomRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Access role refers to the room that the only escape route from an inner room passes through."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AccessRoomRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "AccessRoomRole"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Accommodation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A utilization purpose for premises providing temporary or permanent residential living."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Accommodation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Accommodation"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#ActiveFireProtectionRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A fire protection role involving active detection, alarm, suppression, control, release, emergency lighting, or operational response. This role is typically assigned to fire protection systems or equipment."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#ActiveFireProtectionRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "ActiveFireProtectionRole"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AlternativeEscapeRouteRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Escape routes that are sufficiently separated by direction and space or by fire resisting construction to ensure that one is still available if the other is affected by fire.\r\nA second stair, balcony or flat roof which enables a person to reach a place free from danger from fire is considered an alternative escape route for the purposes of a dwellinghouse."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AlternativeEscapeRouteRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "AlternativeEscapeRouteRole"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AlternativeExitRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "One of two or more exits, each of which is separate from the other."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AlternativeExitRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "AlternativeExitRole"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Applicable> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An applicability state indicating that the requirement, rule, or assessment condition applies in the given context."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Applicable> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Applicable"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AssemblyPlace> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A utilization purpose for premises used for public assembly, entertainment, or recreation."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#AssemblyPlace> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "AssemblyPlace"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Auditorium> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An auditorium is a large room or building designed for public gatherings, such as performances, lectures, or meetings."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Auditorium> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Auditorium"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Bathroom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "a room for washing and personal hygiene, typically containing a toilet, sink, and either a bathtub or shower."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Bathroom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Bathroom"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#BoardingHouse> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A utilization purpose for premises providing lodging and meals for paying guests."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#BoardingHouse> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "BoardingHouse"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#BoilerRoom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A boiler room is a dedicated space in a building that houses essential mechanical equipment for services like heating, hot water, and electricity"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#BoilerRoom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "BoilerRoom"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#CarParking> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A utilization purpose for premises designed for vehicle parking and storage."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#CarParking> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "CarParking"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#CavityBarrierPerformanceAspect> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Assumption that internal cavities are adequately sealed by cavity barriers and do not provide a path for fire spread."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#CavityBarrierPerformanceAspect> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "CavityBarrierPerformanceAspect"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#CirculationSpaceRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Circulation space refers to a space (including a protected stairway) mainly used as a means of access between a room and an exit from the building or compartment."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#CirculationSpaceRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "CirculationSpaceRole"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#CirculationUsage> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A space usage for areas primarily serving pedestrian movement, such as corridors, halls, and lobbies."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#CirculationUsage> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "CirculationUsage"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#CommercialPlace> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A utilization purpose for premises used for commercial trading activities."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#CommercialPlace> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "CommercialPlace"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#CompartmentationPerformanceAspect> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Assumption that floor and wall partitions maintain fire compartmentation and prevent vertical or horizontal fire spread."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#CompartmentationPerformanceAspect> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "CompartmentationPerformanceAspect"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#CompliantResult> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A compliance result indicating that the assessed element or system meets the applicable regulatory requirement."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#CompliantResult> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "CompliantResult"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Compromised> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A condition state indicating that the physical performance of a boundary element is degraded or unreliable."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Compromised> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Compromised"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Corridor> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A corridor is a long, narrow passageway in a building that connects different rooms or areas.\r\nA design of a building containing flats, in which each flat is approached via a common horizontal internal access or circulation space, which may include a common entrance hall."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Corridor> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Corridor"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#DeadEndRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An area from which escape is possible in one direction only."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#DeadEndRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "DeadEndRole"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#DetentionHouse> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A utilization purpose for premises used for lawful detention of persons."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#DetentionHouse> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "DetentionHouse"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Dwellinghouse> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Does not include a flat or a building containing a flat."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Dwellinghouse> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Dwellinghouse"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Effective> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A condition state indicating that the physical performance of a boundary element is intact and functioning as designed."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Effective> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Effective"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#EngineRoom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "In buildings, an \"engine room\" typically refers to the central location for the mechanical and electrical systems that keep the building running, such as HVAC, boilers, generators, and pumps."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#EngineRoom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "EngineRoom"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#EntertainmentPlace> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A utilization purpose for premises used for entertainment or recreational activities."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#EntertainmentPlace> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "EntertainmentPlace"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#EntranceHall> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A hall or space inside a dwelling that connects\r\nthe entrance door to the rooms."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#EntranceHall> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "EntranceHall"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#EvacuationRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The route along which people can escape from any point in a building to a final exit."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#EvacuationRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "EvacuationRole"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#EvidenceAvailable> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An evidence status indicating that supporting evidence is available for the finding or record."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#EvidenceAvailable> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "EvidenceAvailable"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#EvidenceInsufficient> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An evidence status indicating that supporting evidence is available but insufficient for the finding or record."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#EvidenceInsufficient> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "EvidenceInsufficient"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#EvidenceMissing> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An evidence status indicating that no supporting evidence is available for the finding or record."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#EvidenceMissing> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "EvidenceMissing"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#EvidenceNotRequired> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An evidence status indicating that supporting evidence is not required for the finding or record."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#EvidenceNotRequired> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "EvidenceNotRequired"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#ExitPassagewayRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A protected passageway that connects a protected stairway to a final exit."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#ExitPassagewayRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "ExitPassagewayRole"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#ExternalFireSpreadPerformanceAspect> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Assumption that the external wall construction does not contribute to external fire spread between compartments or buildings."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#ExternalFireSpreadPerformanceAspect> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "ExternalFireSpreadPerformanceAspect"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Factory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Assumption that the external wall construction does not contribute to external fire spread between compartments or buildings."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Factory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Factory"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#FinalExitRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The end of an escape route from a building that gives direct access to a street, passageway, walkway or open space, and is sited to ensure that people rapidly disperse away from the building so that they are no longer in danger from fire and/or smoke.\r\nWindows are not acceptable as final exits."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#FinalExitRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "FinalExitRole"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#FireResistingRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A fire protection role indicating that an object is required or designated to provide fire resistance for a stated period according to relevant performance criteria."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#FireResistingRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "FireResistingRole"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#FireSeparatingRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A fire protection role indicating that an object contributes to fire separation or compartmentation, such as a compartment wall, compartment floor, cavity barrier, or enclosing construction for a protected route or special hazard."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#FireSeparatingRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "FireSeparatingRole"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#FirefightingRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Firefighting in buildings is the strategic and tactical process used by the fire and rescue service to control and extinguish fires, protect lives and property, and manage associated hazards within a built structure."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#FirefightingRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "FirefightingRole"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Flat> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A flat is a separate and self-contained premises constructed or adapted for use for residential purposes and forming part of a building from some other part of which it is divided horizontally."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Flat> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Flat"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Foyer> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The large area where people meet or wait just inside the main doors of a building." .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Foyer> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Foyer"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#FuelStorage> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Fuel storage in buildings refers to the secure and safe storage of various fuels, such as oil, petrol, or wood, for heating, cooking, or other purposes."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#FuelStorage> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "FuelStorage"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Gallery> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A floor or balcony that does not extend across the full extent of a building’s footprint and is open to the floor below."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Gallery> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Gallery"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#HabitableRoom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A room used, or intended to be used, for people to live in (including, for the purposes of Approved Document B Volumes 1 and 2, a kitchen, but not a bathroom)."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#HabitableRoom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "HabitableRoom"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Hall> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A \"hall\" in a building can refer to a large, central room or a long, narrow passageway."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Hall> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Hall"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#HallOfResidence> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A utilization purpose for institutional residential accommodation, typically for students or workers."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#HallOfResidence> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "HallOfResidence"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Hospital> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A utilization purpose for premises providing medical treatment, care, or maintenance of persons."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Hospital> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Hospital"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Hostel> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A utilization purpose for premises providing basic shared accommodation."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Hostel> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Hostel"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Hotel> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A utilization purpose for premises providing temporary guest accommodation with services."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Hotel> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Hotel"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Impaired> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The system is out of service, degraded, or bypassed."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Impaired> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Impaired"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#ImpairmentUnknown> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The operational state cannot be determined."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#ImpairmentUnknown> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "ImpairmentUnknown"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#InnerRoomRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Inner room refers to Room from which escape is possible only by passing through another room (the access room)."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#InnerRoomRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "InnerRoomRole"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#InstallationNotRequired> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An installation status indicating that installation of the system or component is not required."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#InstallationNotRequired> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "InstallationNotRequired"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#InstallationUnknown> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An installation status indicating that whether the system or component is installed is unknown."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#InstallationUnknown> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "InstallationUnknown"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Installed> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An installation status indicating that the system or component is installed."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Installed> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Installed"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Kitchen> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A room for food preparation."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Kitchen> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Kitchen"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Lobby> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A lobby is the large, open space at the main entrance of a building that serves as an entry hall, gathering area, and passageway."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Lobby> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Lobby"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#MeansOfEscapeRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Structural means that provide one or more safe routes for people to go, during a fire, from any point in the building to a place of safety."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#MeansOfEscapeRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "MeansOfEscapeRole"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#NonCompliantResult> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A compliance result indicating that the assessed element or system does not meet the applicable regulatory requirement."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#NonCompliantResult> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "NonCompliantResult"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#NotApplicable> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An applicability state indicating that the requirement, rule, or assessment condition does not apply in the given context."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#NotApplicable> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "NotApplicable"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#NotAssessed> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An applicability state indicating that applicability has not yet been assessed for the requirement, rule, or condition."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#NotAssessed> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "NotAssessed"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#NotInstalled> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An installation status indicating that the system or component is not installed."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#NotInstalled> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "NotInstalled"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Office> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Offices or premises used for any of the following and their control:\r\n• administration\r\n• clerical work (including writing, bookkeeping, sorting papers, filing, typing, duplicating, machine calculating, drawing and the editorial preparation of matter for publication, police and fire and rescue service work)\r\n• handling money (including banking and building society work)\r\n• communications (including postal, telegraph and radio communications)\r\n• radio, television, film, audio or video recording\r\n• performance (premises not open to the public)."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Office> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Office"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Operational> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The system is functioning as designed."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Operational> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Operational"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PartiallyInstalled> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An installation status indicating that the system or component is only partially installed."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PartiallyInstalled> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "PartiallyInstalled"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PassiveFireProtectionRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A fire protection role involving passive construction, separation, enclosure, fire resistance, cavity protection, fire stopping, protected routes, or protected spaces. This role may be assigned to physical objects, zones, or systems depending on the assessment context."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PassiveFireProtectionRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "PassiveFireProtectionRole"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PlaceOfSpecialHazard> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A room such as any of the following.\r\n• Oil-filled transformer room.\r\n• Switch gear room.\r\n• Boiler room.\r\n• Storage space for fuel or other highly flammable substance(s).\r\n• Room that houses a fixed internal combustion engine."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PlaceOfSpecialHazard> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "PlaceOfSpecialHazard"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PurposeGroup1a> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A flat is a separate and self-contained premises constructed or adapted for use for residential purposes and forming part of a building from some other part of which it is divided horizontally."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PurposeGroup1a> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "PurposeGroup1a"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PurposeGroup1b> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Dwellinghouse that contains a habitable storey with a floor level a minimum of 4.5m above ground level up to a maximum of 18m."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PurposeGroup1b> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "PurposeGroup1b"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PurposeGroup1c> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Dwellinghouse that does not contain a habitable storey with a floor level a minimum of 4.5m above ground level."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PurposeGroup1c> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "PurposeGroup1c"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PurposeGroup2a> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Hospital, home, school or other similar establishment, where people sleep on the premises. The building may be either of the following:\r\n• Living accommodation for, or accommodation for the treatment, care or maintenance of, either:\r\n    - disabled people with a range of impairments including physical, sensory and\r\ncognitive impairments, or mental health conditions\r\n    - people under the age of 5 years.\r\n• A place of lawful detention."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PurposeGroup2a> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "PurposeGroup2a"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PurposeGroup2b> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Hotel, boarding house, residential college, hall of residence, hostel or any other residential purpose not described above."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PurposeGroup2b> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "PurposeGroup2b"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PurposeGroup3> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Offices or premises used for any of the following and their control:\r\n• administration\r\n• clerical work (including writing, bookkeeping, sorting papers, filing, typing, duplicating, machine calculating, drawing and the editorial preparation of matter for publication, police and fire and rescue service work)\r\n• handling money (including banking and building society work)\r\n• communications (including postal, telegraph and radio communications)\r\n• radio, television, film, audio or video recording\r\n• performance (premises not open to the public)."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PurposeGroup3> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "PurposeGroup3"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PurposeGroup4> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Shops or premises used for either of the following.\r\n• A retail trade or business (including selling food or drink to the public for immediate consumption, retail by auction, self-selection and over-the-counter wholesale trading, the business of lending books or periodicals for gain, the business of a barber or hairdresser, and the rental of storage space to the public).\r\n• Premises to which the public are invited either:\r\n    – to deliver or collect goods in connection with their hire, repair or other treatment\r\n    – (except in the case of repair of motor vehicles) where the public themselves may carry out such repairs or other treatments."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PurposeGroup4> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "PurposeGroup4"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PurposeGroup5> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Place of assembly, entertainment or recreation, including any of the following:\r\n• bingo halls, broadcasting, recording and film studios open to the public, casinos, dance halls\r\n• entertainment, conference, exhibition and leisure centres\r\n• funfairs and amusement arcades\r\n• museums and art galleries, non-residential clubs, theatres, cinemas, concert halls\r\n• educational establishments, dancing schools, gymnasia, swimming pool buildings, riding schools, skating rinks, sports pavilions, sports stadia\r\n• law courts\r\n• churches and other buildings of worship, crematoria\r\n• libraries open to the public, non-residential day centres, clinics, health centres and surgeries\r\n• passenger stations and termini for air, rail, road or sea travel\r\n• public toilets\r\n• zoos and menageries."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PurposeGroup5> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "PurposeGroup5"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PurposeGroup6> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Factories and other premises used for any of the following:\r\n• manufacturing, altering, repairing, cleaning, washing, breaking up, adapting or processing any article\r\n• generating power\r\n• slaughtering livestock."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PurposeGroup6> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "PurposeGroup6"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PurposeGroup7a> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Either of the following:\r\n• place (other than described under 7(b)) for the storage or deposit of goods or materials\r\n• any building not within purpose groups 1 to 6."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PurposeGroup7a> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "PurposeGroup7a"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PurposeGroup7b> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Car parks designed to admit and accommodate only cars, motorcycles and passenger or light goods vehicles that weigh a maximum of 2500kg gross."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#PurposeGroup7b> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "PurposeGroup7b"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#ResidentialCollege> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A utilization purpose for a college providing on-site residential accommodation for students."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#ResidentialCollege> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "ResidentialCollege"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#School> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A place of education for children between 2 and 19 years old. The term includes nursery schools, primary schools and secondary schools as defined in the Education Act 1996."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#School> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "School"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#ServiceUsage> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A space usage for rooms primarily housing building services equipment and infrastructure."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#ServiceUsage> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "ServiceUsage"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#ShelteredHousing> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Includes two or more dwellings in the same building or on adjacent sites, designed and constructed as residential accommodation for vulnerable or elderly people who receive, or will receive, a support service."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#ShelteredHousing> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "ShelteredHousing"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Shop> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Shops or premises used for either of the following.\r\n• A retail trade or business (including selling food or drink to the public for immediate consumption, retail by auction, self-selection and over the-counter wholesale trading, the business of lending books or periodicals for gain, the business of a barber or hairdresser, and the rental of storage space to the public).\r\n• Premises to which the public are invited either:\r\n– to deliver or collect goods in connection with their hire, repair or other treatment\r\n– (except in the case of repair of motor vehicles) where the public themselves may carry out such repairs or other treatments."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Shop> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Shop"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Storage> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A utilization purpose for premises used for storing goods or materials."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Storage> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Storage"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#StoreyExitRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A final exit, or a doorway that gives direct access into a protected stairway, firefighting lobby or external escape route.\r\nNOTE: If an institutional building is planned to enable progressive horizontal evacuation, a door in a compartment wall is considered a storey exit for the purposes of requirement B1."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#StoreyExitRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "StoreyExitRole"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#StructuralStabilityPerformanceAspect> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Assumption that the building structure maintains load-bearing stability for the required period during a fire event."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#StructuralStabilityPerformanceAspect> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "StructuralStabilityPerformanceAspect"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#SwitchGearRoom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A switchgear room in a building is a dedicated space that houses electrical equipment used to control, protect, and isolate the building's electrical system, such as circuit breakers, switches, and fuses."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#SwitchGearRoom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "SwitchGearRoom"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#TransformerRoom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A transformer room is a dedicated space within a building that houses transformers and associated electrical equipment to step down high-voltage electricity from the grid to a usable low voltage for the building."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#TransformerRoom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "TransformerRoom"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#UndeterminedResult> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A compliance result indicating that the compliance status could not be determined from available evidence."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#UndeterminedResult> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "UndeterminedResult"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Unknown> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A condition state indicating that the physical condition of a boundary element cannot be determined from available evidence."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Unknown> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Unknown"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#UnprotectedAreaRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Unprotected area (in relation to a side or external wall of a building) All of the following are classed as unprotected areas.\r\n• Any part of the external wall that has less than the relevant fire resistance set out in Section 11.\r\n• Any part of the external wall constructed of material more than 1mm thick if that material does not have a class B-s3, d2 rating or better, which is attached or applied, whether for cladding or any other purpose.\r\n• Windows, doors or other openings. This does not include windows that are designed and glazed to give the necessary level of fire resistance and that are not openable.\r\nNOTE: Recessed car parking areas as shown in\r\nDiagram A1 should not be regarded as unprotected\r\nareas."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#UnprotectedAreaRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "UnprotectedAreaRole"@en .
# 
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Warehouse> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A warehouse is a large building used for storing goods, such as raw materials, finished products, or equipment, until they are needed for manufacturing, distribution, or sale."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ficr#Warehouse> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Warehouse"@en .
